profile_positions.description:
Business development & fundraising:
- Develop and maintain a Contributor and fundraising pipeline, recording material interactions with leads, prospects and Contributors, and donors in CRM database;
- Assist the Directors in business development and fundraising activities, from meeting coordination to adequate follow-up, and in the case of donor accounts, the grant development process.

Developing and leading strategic engagement:
- Develop and implement an engagement strategy focussed on OCA's key stakeholder groups, including recruitment, onboarding and engagement of Contributors for OCA globally;
- Review and improve processes and tools for engagement on OCA's platform and our principal Farm Programme;
- Support the development of educational and marketing collateral needed for dissemination of OCA information to key stakeholders;
- Establish a system to regularly monitor the satisfaction levels of OCA Contributors.

Account management:
- Foster a positive Contributor experience from onboarding onward and build substantive relationships to increase engagement and retention;
- Conduct regular touch-bases with Contributors to understand their priorities, concerns, challenges and opportunities, allowing OCA to improve service delivery, anticipate and respond to evolving needs;
- Maintain and evolve OCA's existing Contributor database in an accurate and timely manner to ensure the most accurate information;
- Collaborate with other OCA teams to ensure each new Contributors' experience is optimal, offering a smooth transition from initial interest/outreach to onboarding:
- Plan and deliver annual OCA Contributor meetings, both virtual and in-person, and support the execution of public events.

·	Project management and coordination of engineering projects through multi-disciplinary teamwork;
·	Environmental compliance on clients’ projects / industrial sites, identifying opportunities, operational risks and proposing mitigation measures;
·	Appraisal of the environmental and social impacts of development projects;
·	Support for clients in the preparation of assessment or monitoring reports for the authorities;
·	Preparation of measurement reports for lenders to release/maintain payment flows;
·	Technical consultancy in permit proceedings and application forms, reaching 98% of approval;
·	Fieldwork coordination and data collection to support technical analysis;
·	Gathering info, documentation analysis and verification of gaps to achieve key performance standards, such as ISO 14000 or IFC Performance Standards;
·	Coordination of several land regularization projects, building trust with stakeholder engagement, positively impacting more than 5.000 families in informal settlements;
·	Drafting reports for key stakeholders and preparation of Environmental Statements for companies;
·	Liaise with companies, government and project-affected communities to foster stakeholder relationships.
·	Participation activities and community consultation, to enhance support from stakeholders;
·	Feasibility analysis of E&S aspects of conception projects, in early stage project development.
·	Strategic advisory and consultancy for sustainable business models, nature-based solutions and ecosystem services.

•	Development of projects and programs focusing on service provision of environmental and engineering projects for industries; real estate companies; infrastructure & public concession (waste treatment and water supply, road and airport services, and energy); rural development & agribusiness and business-to-customer services.
•	Direct sales to existing clients as well as expanding Florestec customer base through public contracts and biddings;
•	Research and development initiatives, connecting scientists, universities and engineers to understand how technical advances in research could be applied to solve practical challenges being faced by correlating operational activities (forest restoration, contaminated site management, and so forth);
•	Expand Florestec’s industry and partner network, managing the portfolio;
•	Support the team with capacity building on Environmental and Social regulations, sustainability issues and business administration;
•	Scope out and develop long term structural plan for the company.

The objective of this regional facility (Coordenadoria de Biodiversidade e Recursos Naturais) was the environmental monitoring of 74 municipalities in a surface coverage around 37,000 km² (approximately 15% of Sao Paulo State), and the responsibilities included:
·	Teamwork coordination;
·	Fieldwork inspections and writing of non-compliance reports;
·	Support for policy making and policy application, contribution to the creation of new policy frameworks, and technical support for regulatory texts;
·	Contributed directly to the monitoring of the environmental management system and support for environmental police forces and justice departments;
·	Designed a local GIS solution to support the compliance check, increasing the effectivity of proceedings by 10%;
·	Expert representative in thematic committees, with both public and private sectors, participating in meetings and conferences.

The objective of this regional facility (Agência Ambiental de Itu) was mainly to run environmental permit application procedures of 11 municipalities, and the responsibilities included:
- Compliance check on real estate projects, industrial sites, and farmlands to assess socio-environmental impacts, in a wide range of economic sectors;
- Data analysis and evaluation of Environmental Impact Assessments; 
- Analysis and decision-making in environmental permits and monitoring E&S impact mitigation measures
- Administrative routines; procurement and budgetary control; 
- Environmental surveys and field inspections on farms, plantations, industries, real estate enterprises, mining sites and public civil works.

Working at one local Centre (Departamento Estadual de Proteção de Recursos Naturais - DEPRN), which included 19 cities in an important environmental region of Sao Paulo State, with strong interconnections of urban expansion, industrial activities, and agriculture. I contributed to redesigning the work division through a rotation-based watershed analysis at a landscape level. So each team member could deliver more efficient outcomes in its region. I was also responsible for: 
- Environmental damage confirmation, its valuation and exploring possibilities for restoration; 
- Providing technical support for environmental permit applications and the administrative process at designated jurisdiction; 
- Environmental surveys and inspections; 
- Environmental reports analysis; 
- Customer service.

·	Supported the environmental and social management, and implemented corrective measures to reduce socio-environmental impacts from visitors in the natural protected area;
·	Liaise with the local smallholders to monitor a project of an alternative source of income (craftsmanship);
·	Surveillance of two thousand hectares of an Atlantic rainforest conservation site; 
·	Drafting of the Annual Operational Report.
